The 53-year-old opted for former Brazil rival Rivelino, famous Uruguayan football commentator Victor Hugo Morales and Oscar-winning actress Julia Roberts.

Whether Hollywood star Roberts takes up Maradona's challenge, which aims to raise awareness for amyotrophic lateral sclerosis (ALS), remains to be seen.

The former Argentina boss becomes the latest in a long line of players and managers to complete the ice bucket challenge, with Lionel Messi, Cristiano Ronaldo and Jose Mourinho among those to have shown their support.

